go vet ./...
```
{% endif %}

## Code Conventions

### Naming
- **Packages:** short, lowercase, no underscores (e.g. `cli`, `config`, `version`)
- **Exported identifiers:** PascalCase (e.g. `Execute`, `Config`, `Load`)
- **Unexported identifiers:** camelCase (e.g. `setupLogging`, `parseLogLevel`)
- **Files:** snake_case matching the primary type/function (e.g. `cli.go`, `cli_test.go`)

### Documentation
- Every exported function/type has a doc comment starting with its name (`// Execute runs...`)
- Package-level doc comment at the top of one file per package

### Error Handling
- Return errors, don't panic, in library code (`internal/*`)
- Wrap errors with context: `fmt.Errorf("loading config: %w", err)`
- Only `cmd/main.go` decides the process exit code

